title.narrative: COMPREHENSIVE HOME VISITING SERVICE

description.narrative: Output 1.3: The patronage nursing system provides a comprehensive range social and health home visiting services to children and their families, which meet international standards., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Early Childhood Development, Evaluation And Research, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: Families with children, adolescents, and young people living close to or below the national subsistence minimum are more resilient (to economic and social deprivation, and stress) and they benefit more from equitable access to quality and inclusive social services and transfers
